Abbreviations and Bibliography
 
I. Abbreviations
 
1C: The Life of Saint Francis by Thomas of Celano
2C: The Remembrance of the Desire of a Soul by Thomas of Celano
3C: The Treatise on the Miracles by Thomas of Celano
AC: The Assisi Compilation
ChrJG: The Chronicle of Jordan of Giano
DBF: The Deeds of Blessed Francis and His Companions
ER: The Earlier Rule
L3C: The Legend of the Three Companions
LJS: The Life of Saint Francis by Julian of Speyer
LMj: The Major Legend by Bonaventure
LMn: The Minor Legend by Bonaventure
LR: The Later Rule
LSC: The Legend of Saint Clare
Off: The Divine Office of Saint Francis by Julian of Speyer
 
II. Bibliography
 
A. Primary Sources
 
Armstrong, Regis, J.A. Wayne Hellmann and William Short, eds. Francis
of Assisi: Early Documents. 4 vols. New York: New City Press, 1999-2002.
 
de Voragine, Jacobus. The Golden Legend: Readings on the Saints. 2
vols. Trans. William Granger Ryan. Princeton: Princeton University
Press, 1993.
 
Fontes Franciscani. Eds. Enrico Menestò and Stefano Brufani. Assisi,
Italy: Edizioni Porziuncola, 1991.
 
Monti, Dominic. Breviloquium. In Works of St. Bonaventure,
vol. IX. St. Bonaventure, NY: Fanciscan Institute Publications, 2005.
 
Pennacchi, Francesco, ed. Legenda Sanctae Clarae Virginis. Assisi:
Società Internazionale di Studi Francescani, 1910.
 
Przewozny, Bernard, ed. Life of St. Anthony, "Assidua" Padua: Edizioni
Messaggero, 1984.
 
Rolandinus, Grammaticus. The Chronicles of the Trevisan
March. Trans. Joseph Berrigan. Lawrence, KS: Coronado Press, 1980.
 
 
